<figureCitation box="[387,453,969,991]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[362,1225,187,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[362,1225,181,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Wings. 1. D. elongata n. sp., holotype female. 2. D. euzona, male. 3. D. potomaca, female. 4. D. sohnsi n. sp., holotype male. Scale bars = ca. 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412967" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412967/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[484,509,969,991]" captionStart="FIGURES 11–12" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1554,1578]" captionTargetBox="[223,1362,182,1525]" captionTargetId="figure-20@6.[220,1367,181,1529]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11–12. D. euzona, male. 11. Habitus. Scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm. 12. Thorax, dorsal. Scale bar = ca. 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412975/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">11</figureCitation>
); male terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[709,823,969,991]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1946,1970]" captionTargetBox="[228,1359,525,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-171@7.[228,1360,525,1923]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. D. euzona, terminalia. 13. Male, lateral. 14. Male, dorsal. 15. Male, ventral. 16. Female, lateral. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: ae, aedeagus; c, cerci; c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; h, hypandrium; hl, hypandrial lobe; p, paramere; s8, sternite eight; t8, tergite eight; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412979" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412979/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Figs. 13–15</figureCitation>
and female terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[1070,1140,969,991]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–16" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1946,1970]" captionTargetBox="[228,1359,525,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-171@7.[228,1360,525,1923]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13–16. D. euzona, terminalia. 13. Male, lateral. 14. Male, dorsal. 15. Male, ventral. 16. Female, lateral. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: ae, aedeagus; c, cerci; c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; h, hypandrium; hl, hypandrial lobe; p, paramere; s8, sternite eight; t8, tergite eight; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412979" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412979/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
; eastern Nearctic…............................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[1278,1437,999,1020]" class="Insecta" family="Ditomyiidae" genus="Ditomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="euzona">
<emphasis box="[1278,1376,999,1020]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">D. euzona</emphasis>
Loew
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,969,1431]" box="[151,1436,1028,1050]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1028,1050]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">- Wing hyaline; terminalia not as above…................................................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,969,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
2 Antennal flagellomeres pale yellow (sometimes becoming light greyish-brown distally), nearly concolorous with pale yellow pedicel and scape, black spot marking base of each antennal seta strongly contrasting against yellow background color of flagellomere (
<figureCitation box="[322,376,1115,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1815,1839]" captionTargetBox="[225,1361,453,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-128@3.[225,1361,453,1792]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Female head, lateral. 5. D. potomaca. 6. D. sohnsi. Scale bars = ca. 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412971/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig 5</figureCitation>
); mesonotum black to very dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[766,836,1116,1138]" captionStart="FIGURE 19" captionStartId="9.[151,250,911,935]" captionTargetBox="[221,1367,182,887]" captionTargetId="figure-15@9.[220,1368,181,888]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 19. D. potomaca, male habitus, lateral. Scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412983" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412983/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
); male terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[1036,1152,1116,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[224,1363,705,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-293@10.[224,1363,705,1918]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. D. potomaca, terminalia. 20. Male, lateral. 21. Male, dorsal. 22. Male, ventral. 23. Female, lateral. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: c, cerci; c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; hl, hypandrial lobe; s8, sternite eight." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412985/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Figs. 20–22</figureCitation>
, female terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[1362,1432,1116,1138]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–23" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1942,1966]" captionTargetBox="[224,1363,705,1915]" captionTargetId="figure-293@10.[224,1363,705,1918]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 20–23. D. potomaca, terminalia. 20. Male, lateral. 21. Male, dorsal. 22. Male, ventral. 23. Female, lateral. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: c, cerci; c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; gc, gonocoxite; gs, gonostylus; hl, hypandrial lobe; s8, sternite eight." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412985" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412985/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
; eastern Nearctic…...................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Fisher" authorityName="Fisher" authorityYear="1941" box="[1246,1436,1145,1167]" class="Insecta" family="Ditomyiidae" genus="Ditomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="potomaca">
<emphasis box="[1246,1371,1146,1167]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">D. potomaca</emphasis>
Fisher
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,969,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
- Antennal flagellomeres grey-brown, contrasting with pale yellow scape and pedicel, black spot marking base of each antennal seta not strongly contrasting against background color of flagellomere (
<figureCitation box="[903,961,1204,1226]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–6" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1815,1839]" captionTargetBox="[225,1361,453,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-128@3.[225,1361,453,1792]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 5–6. Female head, lateral. 5. D. potomaca. 6. D. sohnsi. Scale bars = ca. 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412971" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412971/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); mesonotum pale yellow with light brown stripes (
<figureCitation box="[233,299,1233,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[248,1341,528,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-181@5.[247,1341,525,1904]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. D. elongata n. sp., holotype female. 7. Habitus. Scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm. 8–10. Female terminalia. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. 8. Dorsal. 9. Ventral. 10. Lateral. Abbreviations: c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; s7, sternite seven; s8, sternite eight; s10, sternite ten; t7, tergite seven; t8, tergite eight, t10, tergite ten." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412973" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412973/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Figs. 7</figureCitation>
&amp; 
<figureCitation box="[330,357,1233,1255]" captionStart="FIGURE 24" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1508,1532]" captionTargetBox="[223,1367,181,1483]" captionTargetId="figure-15@11.[220,1368,181,1484]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 24. D. sohnsi n. sp., female habitus, lateral. Scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412989" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412989/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">24</figureCitation>
); western Nearctic…........................................................................ 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,969,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
3 Macrotrichia of wing evenly distributed on basal third (cell br+bm with evenly spaced macrotrichia) (
<figureCitation box="[1208,1267,1262,1284]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[362,1225,187,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[362,1225,181,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Wings. 1. D. elongata n. sp., holotype female. 2. D. euzona, male. 3. D. potomaca, female. 4. D. sohnsi n. sp., holotype male. Scale bars = ca. 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412967" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412967/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); male terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[253,370,1291,1314]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[220,1371,689,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-261@12.[216,1371,669,1852]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. D. sohnsi n. sp., terminalia. 25. Male, lateral. 26. Male, dorsal. 27. Male, ventral. 28. Female, lateral. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: ae, aedeagus; c, cerci; c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; ea, ejaculatory apodeme; gc, gonocoxite; gsi, inner lobe of gonostylus; gso, outer lobe of gonostylus; h, hypandrium; hl, hypandrial lobe; p, paramere; s8, sternite eight; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412991/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Figs. 25–27</figureCitation>
, female terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[584,655,1292,1314]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–28" captionStartId="12.[151,264,1875,1899]" captionTargetBox="[220,1371,689,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-261@12.[216,1371,669,1852]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 25–28. D. sohnsi n. sp., terminalia. 25. Male, lateral. 26. Male, dorsal. 27. Male, ventral. 28. Female, lateral. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. Abbreviations: ae, aedeagus; c, cerci; c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; ea, ejaculatory apodeme; gc, gonocoxite; gsi, inner lobe of gonostylus; gso, outer lobe of gonostylus; h, hypandrium; hl, hypandrial lobe; p, paramere; s8, sternite eight; t9, tergite nine." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412991" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412991/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
, with second segment of cerci broadly rounded and not tapered apically; female fore tibia ~1.1 times as long as fore basitarsus; 
<collectingRegion box="[679,845,1321,1343]" country="Canada" name="British Columbia" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">British Columbia</collectingRegion>
to 
<collectingRegion box="[875,972,1321,1343]" country="United States of America" name="California" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">California</collectingRegion>
............... … 
