</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,969,1431]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<keyLead pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,159,1350,1371]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">-</emphasis>
Basal third of wing with macrotrichia unevenly distributed and with large bare areas (cell br+bm mostly bare) (
<figureCitation box="[1310,1367,1350,1372]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1789,1813]" captionTargetBox="[362,1225,187,1763]" captionTargetId="figure-20@2.[362,1225,181,1766]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Wings. 1. D. elongata n. sp., holotype female. 2. D. euzona, male. 3. D. potomaca, female. 4. D. sohnsi n. sp., holotype male. Scale bars = ca. 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412967" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412967/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); male unknown; female terminalia as 
<figureCitation box="[527,631,1380,1402]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[248,1341,528,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-181@5.[247,1341,525,1904]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. D. elongata n. sp., holotype female. 7. Habitus. Scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm. 8–10. Female terminalia. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. 8. Dorsal. 9. Ventral. 10. Lateral. Abbreviations: c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; s7, sternite seven; s8, sternite eight; s10, sternite ten; t7, tergite seven; t8, tergite eight, t10, tergite ten." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412973" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412973/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Figs. 8–10</figureCitation>
, with second cercus more narrow and slightly tapered to a round point apically (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[248,1341,528,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-181@5.[247,1341,525,1904]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. D. elongata n. sp., holotype female. 7. Habitus. Scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm. 8–10. Female terminalia. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. 8. Dorsal. 9. Ventral. 10. Lateral. Abbreviations: c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; s7, sternite seven; s8, sternite eight; s10, sternite ten; t7, tergite seven; t8, tergite eight, t10, tergite ten." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412973" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412973/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
); female fore tibia ~1.5 times as long as fore basitarsus (
<figureCitation box="[795,854,1409,1431]" captionStart="FIGURES 7–10" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1927,1951]" captionTargetBox="[248,1341,528,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-181@5.[247,1341,525,1904]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 7–10. D. elongata n. sp., holotype female. 7. Habitus. Scale bar = ca. 1.0 mm. 8–10. Female terminalia. Scale bars = ca. 0.25 mm. 8. Dorsal. 9. Ventral. 10. Lateral. Abbreviations: c1, cercus one; c2, cercus two; s7, sternite seven; s8, sternite eight; s10, sternite ten; t7, tergite seven; t8, tergite eight, t10, tergite ten." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4412973" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4412973/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
); 
<collectingRegion box="[872,991,1409,1431]" country="United States of America" name="Washington" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Washington</collectingRegion>
…............ 
